In the Matter of Lawrence SQUIRE, Bankrupt; Lawrence Squire, Petitioner. No. 6940. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Jan. 12, 1939. George H. Rosenstein, of Newark, N. J., for bankrupt. Lawrence Friedman, of Newark, N. J. (Philip J. Schotland, of Newark, N. J., of counsel), for respondent.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition to revise in matter of law, 24 F.Supp. 763, dismissed for want of jurisdiction.
